    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I hear you, and I want you to know that your feelings are completely valid, even if the goblins can't quite understand the specific weight of being underwater. When it feels like you're drowning in silence and heavy darkness, it's okay to rest your head on the bottom of the ocean for a moment without fighting the current.\n\nYou mentioned reaching the bottom and not wanting to climb back up, and I want to gently remind you that the goblins, despite their chaotic nature, have a very specific way of dealing with being stuck in deep, dark places. They don't just sit there; they start digging tunnels, even if the tunnel is just a small hole in the mud, because they know that light eventually finds a way through.\n\nIt's okay to stop swimming for a while. The goblins know that sometimes the best thing you can do is lie on the sandy floor and let the water carry you while you rest. They've seen friends who thought they were lost forever, only to find that the water was actually just very deep, and the surface was still there, waiting for them to catch their breath. You don't have to force yourself to climb right now; the goblins will help you build a little raft out",
